  <section>
    <h2>VB Underline Styles</h2>
    <p>VB uses six distinct underline styles across its text elements. Each has a unique visual treatment so users can distinguish their meaning at a glance:</p>

    <table class="props-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Element</th>
          <th>Style</th>
          <th>Color</th>
          <th>Use Case</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><code>&lt;u&gt;</code></td>
          <td>Wavy</td>
          <td>Red (<code>oklch(55% 0.2 25)</code>)</td>
          <td>Spelling errors, annotations</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>&lt;a&gt;</code></td>
          <td>Solid (1px&rarr;2px on hover)</td>
          <td><code>var(--color-interactive)</code></td>
          <td>Hyperlinks</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>&lt;abbr&gt;</code></td>
          <td>Dotted</td>
          <td><code>var(--color-text-muted)</code></td>
          <td>Abbreviations with tooltip</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>&lt;ins&gt;</code></td>
          <td>Solid bottom border</td>
          <td>Green (<code>oklch(60% 0.18 145)</code>)</td>
          <td>Inserted text (editorial)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>&lt;s&gt;</code></td>
          <td>Line-through</td>
          <td><code>var(--color-text-muted)</code></td>
          <td>No longer relevant</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>&lt;del&gt;</code></td>
          <td>Line-through + background</td>
          <td>Red (<code>oklch(55% 0.2 25)</code>)</td>
          <td>Deleted text (editorial)</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>CSS Reference</h2>
    <code-block language="css" label="u CSS">{{ uCssCode | escape }}</code-block>
    <p>The wavy style with red color matches the universal spell-check convention used by browsers, word processors, and IDEs.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Accessibility</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Screen readers typically do <strong>not</strong> announce the underline</li>
      <li>The visual is a cue only &mdash; provide text context for important annotations</li>
      <li>For educational content, add <code>visually-hidden</code> context:</li>
    </ul>

    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Accessible annotation">{{ accessibleCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

